plot.formatting <- function (){ # Based on bbc_style(), then modified for clarity
    font <- "sans"
    sz.big <- 13
    sz.small <- 11
    ggplot2::theme(plot.title = ggplot2::element_text(family = font, size = sz.big, face = "bold", color = "black"), 
        plot.subtitle = ggplot2::element_text(family = font, size = sz.big, margin = ggplot2::margin(9, 0, 9, 0)), 
        plot.caption = ggplot2::element_blank(),
        legend.position = "right", legend.text.align = 0, 
        legend.background = ggplot2::element_blank(),
        legend.title = ggplot2::element_text(family = font, size = sz.big, color = "black"), 
        legend.key = ggplot2::element_blank(),
        legend.text = ggplot2::element_text(family = font, size = sz.small, color = "black"), 
        axis.title = ggplot2::element_text(family = font, size = sz.big, color = "black"),
        axis.text = ggplot2::element_text(family = font, size = sz.small, color = "black"), 
        axis.text.x = ggplot2::element_text(margin = ggplot2::margin(5, b = 10)), 
        axis.line = ggplot2::element_line(color = "black"), 
        panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major.y = ggplot2::element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
        panel.background = ggplot2::element_blank(),
        strip.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill = 'white', linetype = 1),
        strip.text = ggplot2::element_text(size = sz.small, hjust = 0.5),
        legend.key.height = unit(0.5, "line"),
        legend.key.width = unit(0.75, "line"),
        legend.margin = margin(t = -10, unit = 'pt'))
}

# Color palette for training dataset:
# Green = starting
# Orange = + adaptive sampling
# Purple = + random sampling
color.palet = c('#168463', '#d95f02', '#7570b3')
# Color for test system variables
color.var = c('#c5e3a6', '#7aa68b', '#044366')
# Color for the cycles: set of 4
color.cyc = c('#cc6633', '#43b32d', '#267399', '#702080')
# Colors shifted
color.shift = c('#842416', '#12d722', '#739eb9')
fig.count = 1
SI.count = 1

Figures are constructed for publication in an Elsevier journal. The requirements for this journal are:

  • single column: 90 mm

  • 1.5 column: 140 mm

  • double column: 190 mm

  • 300 DPI = halftone

  • 500 DPI = color/combination

  • 1000 DPI = line art

  • .jpg and .tif files - tif for most color images

For the purposes of maintaining resolution, images are scaled up by 50% (eg. 90 mm figures exported at 135). These images can then be scaled down as needed.

# Figure S01a: contours of the polynomial system
frnt = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/Ex_Quartic/GPar_fnt_start.csv')
data = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/Ex_Quartic/GPar_all_start.csv')

# Objective functions are based on the quadratic functions used previously, but with an additional local minimum
f1 = function(x1, x2){
  return(20*(x1 - 0.75)^2 + 190 + 11.58*x2^4 - 115.85*x2^3 + 383.13*x2^2 - 463.50*x2)
}
# The second objective function is also partially rotated so the local optimum is not perfectly aligned
f2 = function(x1, x2){
  # Remap both variables: rotate 30 degrees counterclockwise
  ang = -pi/24
  n1 = x1*cos(ang) - x2*sin(ang)
  n2 = x1*sin(ang) + x2*cos(ang)
  # return((x1 - 2.5)^2 + 80 + 1.778*x2^4 - 20*x2^3 + 78.573*x2^2 - 124.664*x2)
  return((n1 - 2.5)^2 + 80 + 1.778*n2^4 - 20*n2^3 + 78.573*n2^2 - 124.664*n2)
}

# Fine grid spacing
sz.fine = 50
x1.rng = seq(from = 0, to = 5, length.out = sz.fine)
x2.rng = seq(from = 0, to = 5, length.out = sz.fine)
con.fine = expand.grid(x1.rng, x2.rng)
con.fine = con.fine[,1:2]
names(con.fine) = c('x1', 'x2')

# Calculate
con.fine$f1 = f1(x1 = con.fine$x1, x2 = con.fine$x2)
con.fine$f2 = f2(x1 = con.fine$x1, x2 = con.fine$x2)
write.csv(con.fine, paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), 'a.csv', sep = ''))

# Set up so that the lowest (more optimal) values are darker. Organize by log values
bin.f1 = seq(from = min(log10(con.fine$f1)), to = max(log10(con.fine$f1)), length.out = 10)
bin.f2 = seq(from = min(log10(con.fine$f2)), to = max(log10(con.fine$f2)), length.out = 10)

fig = ggplot()
for(i in 1:length(bin.f1)){
    fig = fig + 
        geom_contour(data = con.fine, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2, z = log10(f1), color = 'f1'), 
                             breaks = bin.f1[1:i], alpha = exp(-i/3)) +
        geom_contour(data = con.fine, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2, z = log10(f2), color = 'f2'), 
                             breaks = bin.f2[1:i], alpha = exp(-i/3))
}
fig.pol = fig +
  labs(x = expression('x'[1]), y = expression('x'[2]), subtitle = 'a) Polynomial System') +
  # geom_point(data = data, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2), color = "black", alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_point(data = frnt, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2), color = 'grey50', alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth(data = frnt, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2), color = "grey50", method = 'loess', formula = (y~x), 
              level = 0.95) +
  scale_color_manual(name = 'Objective', values = c('f1' = 'red', 'f2' = 'blue'), 
                     labels = c('f1' = expression('F'[1]), 'f2' = expression('F'[2]))) +
  theme(legend.position = c(0.9, 0.85), legend.background = element_rect(fill = 'white')) +
  scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0, 0)) + scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0)) +
  plot.formatting() + coord_fixed() + guides(color = FALSE)
rm(fig)

# Figure S01bc: contours of the center slide of the modified ZDT4 system (and the original ZDT4 system)
frnt = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/Ex_ZDT4/GPar_fnt_start.csv')

ZDT4.mod = function (x) 
{
  if (is.null(dim(x))) {
    x <- matrix(x, nrow = 1)
  }
  n <- ncol(x)
  g <- 1 + 10 * (n - 1) + rowSums((x[, 2:n, drop = FALSE] * 
    0.5 - 0.25)^2 - 10 * cos(0.5 * pi * (x[, 2:n, drop = FALSE] * 
    10 - 5)))
  return(cbind(x[, 1], g * (1 - sqrt(x[, 1]/g))))
}

# Original function is just ZDT4

# Fine grid spacing
sz.fine = 75
x1.rng = seq(from = 0, to = 1, length.out = sz.fine)
x2.rng = seq(from = 0, to = 1, length.out = sz.fine)
# x3.rng = seq(from = 0, to = 1, length.out = 5)
# x3.rng = unique(c(x3.rng, unique(GPar.front$x3)))
x3.rng = 0.5 # Simple slice for visualization
con.fine = expand.grid(x1.rng, x2.rng, x3.rng)
con.fine = con.fine[,1:3]
names(con.fine) = c('x1', 'x2', 'x3')

# Calculate
res = ZDT4(x = as.matrix(con.fine))
con.fine$f1 = res[,1]; con.fine$f2 = res[,2]
con.fine$f2 = con.fine$f2/max(con.fine$f2)
res = ZDT4.mod(x = as.matrix(con.fine))
con.fine.mod = con.fine
con.fine.mod$f1 = res[,1]; con.fine.mod$f2 = res[,2]
con.fine.mod$f2 = con.fine.mod$f2/max(con.fine.mod$f2)
# Combine
con.fine$typ = 'Original'
con.fine.mod$typ = 'Modified'
con.fine = rbind(con.fine, con.fine.mod)
rm(con.fine.mod)

write.csv(con.fine, paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), 'bc.csv', sep = ''))

# Set the boundaries for f2
f1.bins = seq(from = (min(con.fine$f1)), to = (max(con.fine$f1)), length.out = 5)
f2.bins = seq(from = (min(con.fine$f2)), to = (max(con.fine$f2)), length.out = 5)

fig.org = ggplot() +
  geom_contour(data = filter(con.fine, typ == 'Original'), 
               mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2, z = f1, color = 'f1'), 
               breaks = f1.bins)
fig.mod = ggplot() +
  geom_contour(data = filter(con.fine, typ == 'Modified'), 
               mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2, z = f1, color = 'f1'), 
               breaks = f1.bins)
for(i in 1:length(f2.bins)){
    fig.org = fig.org + 
        geom_contour(data = filter(con.fine, typ == 'Original'),
                     mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2, z = (f2), color = 'f2'), 
                     breaks = f2.bins[1:i], alpha = exp(-i/1.5))
    fig.mod = fig.mod + 
        geom_contour(data = filter(con.fine, typ == 'Modified'),
                     mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2, z = (f2), color = 'f2'), 
                     breaks = f2.bins[1:i], alpha = exp(-i/1.5))

}
fig.org = fig.org +
  geom_point(data = frnt, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2), color = 'grey50', alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth(data = frnt, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2), color = "grey50", method = 'loess', formula = (y~x), 
              level = 0.95) +
  labs(x = expression('x'[1]), y = expression('x'[2]), subtitle = 'c) Original ZDT4') +
  scale_color_manual(name = 'Objective', values = c('f1' = 'red', 'f2' = 'blue'), 
                     labels = c('f1' = expression('F'[1]), 'f2' = expression('F'[2]))) +
  plot.formatting() + coord_fixed() + guides(color = FALSE) +
  theme(strip.text = element_text(hjust = 0),
          strip.background = element_blank()) +
  scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0, 0), breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1)) + 
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0), breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1))

fig.mod = fig.mod +
  geom_point(data = frnt, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2), color = 'grey50', alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_smooth(data = frnt, mapping = aes(x = x1, y = x2), color = "grey50", method = 'loess', formula = (y~x), 
              level = 0.95) +
  labs(x = expression('x'[1]), y = expression('x'[2]), subtitle = 'b) Modified ZDT4') +
  scale_color_manual(name = 'Objective', values = c('f1' = 'red', 'f2' = 'blue'), 
                     labels = c('f1' = expression('F'[1]), 'f2' = expression('F'[2]))) +
  plot.formatting() + coord_fixed() +
  theme(strip.text = element_text(hjust = 0),
          strip.background = element_blank()) +
  scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0, 0), breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1)) + 
  scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0), breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1))

# Combine figures
fig.pol + fig.mod + fig.org + plot_layout(guides = 'collect')


# Figure S01def: Classifier definitions using the polynomial system examples
frnt = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/Ex_Quartic/GPar_fnt_start.csv')
data = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/Ex_Quartic/GPar_all_start.csv')

# Calculate the boundary for the distance < 1 category
# Add 1 unit distance in the same angle (ie. same f1/f2 ratio)

# f1' = 
# (f1/f2*f2')^2 + f2'^2) = (sqrt(f1^2 + f2^2) + 1)^2
# f2'^2  = (sqrt(f1^2 + f2^2) + 1)^2 / ( (f1/f2)^2 + 1)
frnt.project = data.frame(f2.norm = sqrt((sqrt(frnt$f1.norm^2 + frnt$f2.norm^2) + 1)^2/
                              ((frnt$f1.norm/frnt$f2.norm)^2 + 1)))
frnt.project$f1.norm = frnt.project$f2.norm * frnt$f1.norm / frnt$f2.norm
frnt.project$f1.norm[is.na(frnt.project$f1.norm)] = 2
frnt.project$f2.norm[is.na(frnt.project$f2.norm)] = 2
# Set up as a polygon for fill
frnt.project = data.frame(f1.norm = c(frnt.project$f1.norm, rev(frnt$f1.norm)),
                          f2.norm = c(frnt.project$f2.norm, rev(frnt$f2.norm)))
# Select a target point for illustration
i = round(nrow(frnt)/3)
select.point = rbind(frnt.project[i,], frnt[i,names(frnt) %in% names(frnt.project)])
ang = atan(select.point$f2.norm/select.point$f1.norm)[1]*180/pi
frnt.project.delta = frnt.project
frnt.project.delta$cat = 'Pareto Distance'

alph = 0.5
plt.delta = ggplot() +
    # All data
    geom_point(data = filter(data, f1.norm < 2.5, f2.norm < 2.5), mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), 
               alpha = 0.5, color = 'grey50') +
    # Region
    geom_polygon(data = frnt.project, mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm, fill = 'delta'), 
                 linetype = 2, alpha = alph, color = color.shift[1]) +
    # Annotation
    geom_line(data = rbind(select.point, data.frame(f1.norm = 0, f2.norm = 0)), 
              mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), linetype = 2) +
    geom_line(data = select.point, mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), color = 'black') +
    geom_text(data = select.point, mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), color = 'black', 
               label = c('|'), size = 5, angle = ang) +
    geom_text(data = select.point, mapping = aes(x = max(f1.norm), y = max(f2.norm)), color = 'black',
              label = expression(paste(delta*' < '*delta*"'")),
              hjust = 0, nudge_x = 0.1, nudge_y = 0.1) +
    labs(x = expression('Normalized f'[1]), y = expression('Normalized f'[2]), 
         subtitle = 'd) Pareto Distance', fill = NULL) +
    coord_fixed() + plot.formatting() +
    scale_fill_manual(values = color.shift[1], labels = 'Pareto Distance') + guides(fill = FALSE) +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = 0), breaks = c(0, 1, 2)) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = 0), breaks = c(0, 1, 2))

# Cutoff threshold
frnt.project = data.frame(f1.norm = c(0, 1, 1), f2.norm = c(1, 1, 0))
frnt.project = data.frame(f1.norm = c(frnt.project$f1.norm, rev(frnt$f1.norm)),
                          f2.norm = c(frnt.project$f2.norm, rev(frnt$f2.norm)))
frnt.project.cutof = frnt.project
frnt.project.cutof$cat = 'Threshold Cutoff'

plt.cutof = ggplot() +
    # All data
    geom_point(data = filter(data, f1.norm < 2.5, f2.norm < 2.5), mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), 
               alpha = 0.5, color = 'grey50') +
    geom_polygon(data = frnt.project, mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm, fill = 'cutof'), linetype = 2, 
                 alpha = alph, color = color.shift[2]) +
    geom_text(mapping = aes(x = 1, y = 1.1), color = 'black', 
               label = c("F < F', F < F'"), hjust = 0.5, vjust = 1, nudge_y = 0.1) +
    labs(x = expression('Normalized f'[1]), y = expression('Normalized f'[2]), 
         subtitle = 'e) Threshold Cutoff', fill = NULL) +
    coord_fixed() + plot.formatting() +
    scale_fill_manual(values = color.shift[2], labels = '') + guides(fill = FALSE) +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = 0), breaks = c(0, 1, 2)) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = 0), breaks = c(0, 1, 2))

# Radius and angle
frnt.project = data.frame(f1.norm = seq(from = 0, to = 1, by = 0.01))
frnt.project$f2.norm = sqrt(1 - frnt.project$f1.norm^2)
frnt.project = data.frame(f1.norm = c(frnt.project$f1.norm, rev(frnt$f1.norm)),
                          f2.norm = c(frnt.project$f2.norm, rev(frnt$f2.norm)))
frnt.project = filter(frnt.project, atan(f2.norm/f1.norm) > 0.2*pi/2)
frnt.project.radan = frnt.project
frnt.project.radan$cat = 'Utopia Distance'

# Points for labels
select.point = frnt.project[40,]
ang = atan(select.point$f2.norm/select.point$f1.norm)[1]*180/pi
select.point2 = filter(frnt.project, f1.norm == max(f1.norm))[1,]
ang2 = atan(select.point2$f2.norm/select.point2$f1.norm)[1]*180/pi

plt.radan = ggplot() +
    # All data
    geom_point(data = filter(data, f1.norm < 2.5, f2.norm < 2.5), mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), 
               alpha = 0.5, color = 'grey50') +
    # Region
    geom_polygon(data = frnt.project, mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm, fill = 'radan'), 
                 linetype = 2, alpha = alph, color = color.shift[3]) +
    # Annotations
    geom_line(data = rbind(select.point, data.frame(f1.norm = 0, f2.norm = 0)), 
              mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), linetype = 2) +
    geom_line(data = select.point, mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), color = 'black') +
    geom_text(data = select.point, mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), color = 'black', 
               label = c('|'), size = 5, angle = ang) +
    geom_text(data = select.point, mapping = aes(x = max(f1.norm), y = max(f2.norm)), color = 'black',
              label = expression(paste("r < r'")), 
              hjust = 0, nudge_x = 0.1, nudge_y = 0.1) +
    
    geom_line(data = rbind(select.point2, data.frame(f1.norm = 0, f2.norm = 0)), 
              mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), linetype = 2) +
    geom_line(data = select.point2, mapping = aes(x = f1.norm, y = f2.norm), color = 'black') +
    geom_text(data = select.point2, mapping = aes(x = max(f1.norm)*3/4, y = max(f2.norm)*3/4), color = 'black', 
               label = c(')'), size = 7, angle = ang2, hjust = 0.5, vjust = 0.5, nudge_y = -0.1) +
    geom_text(data = select.point2, mapping = aes(x = max(f1.norm)*3/4, y = max(f2.norm)*3/4), color = 'black',
              label = expression(paste(theta*" >"*theta*"'")), 
              hjust = 0, nudge_x = 0.1, nudge_y = -0.1) +
    labs(x = expression('Normalized f'[1]), y = expression('Normalized f'[2]), 
         subtitle = 'f) Utopia Distance', fill = NULL) +
    coord_fixed() + plot.formatting() +
    scale_fill_manual(values = color.shift[3], labels = '') + guides(fill = FALSE) +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = 0), breaks = c(0, 1, 2)) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = 0), breaks = c(0, 1, 2))

fig.pol + fig.mod + fig.org + plt.delta + plt.cutof + plt.radan + 
    plot_layout(widths = 1, guides = 'collect') & 
    theme(legend.box.margin = margin(b = 75, unit = 'mm'))

ggsave(filename = paste('FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
       dpi = 500, width = 190*1.5, height = 105*1.5, units = 'mm')

          paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), 'def.csv', sep = ''))

rm(frnt.project.cutof, frnt.project.delta, frnt.project.radan)
rm(select.point, select.point2, ang, ang2, res, con.fine)

# Figure 4: Accuracy with ZDT4 test system. Only for the cutoff threshold case. Columns: classification model. Colors: before/after/random sampling.

# Load data
data = read.csv(file = '../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_ZDT4/GP_ErrorRate.csv')
data$mod = 'GP'
data = rbind(data,
             read.csv(file = '../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_ZDT4/SVM_ErrorRate.csv'))
# Update column names and data to be in line with Figure 1
data = filter(data, mod != 'lin', mod != 'sig')
data$mod[data$mod != 'GP'] = paste('SVM-', data$mod[data$mod != 'GP'], sep = '')

# Create a dummy variable for the bounds
dummy = expand.grid(unique(data$cat), unique(data$mod), unique(data$class))
names(dummy) = c('cat', 'mod', 'class')
n = nrow(dummy)
dummy = rbind(dummy, dummy)
dummy$prob = 0; dummy$prob[1:n] = 1
dummy$prob[dummy$class == 'Utopia Distance'] = dummy$prob[dummy$class == 'Utopia Distance']*0.4

# data
ggplot(filter(data, typ == 'Total')) +
    geom_col(mapping = aes(x = factor(cat, levels = c('paret', 'adapt', 'rando')), 
                           fill = factor(cat, levels = c('paret', 'adapt', 'rando')), y = prob)) +
    geom_errorbar(mapping = aes(ymin = prob - err, ymax = prob + err, 
                                x = factor(cat, levels = c('paret', 'adapt', 'rando'))), width = 0.5) +
    facet_rep_grid(class~mod, scales = 'free_y', switch = 'y') +
    labs(x = 'Training Data:', y = 'Misclassification Error Rates') +
  # blank data to fix bounds
  geom_blank(data = dummy,
             mapping = aes(x = cat, y = prob)) +
    scale_x_discrete(labels = NULL) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.05))) +
    scale_fill_manual(name = '',
                        labels = c('Start',
                                 'Start + Adaptive Sampling',
                                 'Start + Random Sampling'),
                        values = color.palet) +
    # scale_x_discrete(labels = NULL) +
    plot.formatting() +
    theme(panel.spacing.y = unit(0.5, "lines"),
          panel.spacing.x = unit(0.00001, "lines"),
          legend.position = 'bottom', legend.direction = 'horizontal',
          legend.box.margin = margin(r = 15, unit = 'mm'),
          strip.placement = 'outside',
          axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = 5, unit = 'pt')))

ggsave(filename = paste('Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
         dpi = 500, width = 135, height = 120, units = 'mm')
write.csv(data, 
          file = paste('Data_Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), 
                       '_S', sprintf('%02d', SI.count),
                       '_S', sprintf('%02d', SI.count+1), '.csv', sep = ''))
fig.count = fig.count + 1

# Figure S5: Accuracy with ZDT4 test system for Pareto distance and utopia distance criteria. Columns: classification model. Colors: before/after/random sampling.

ggplot(filter(data, typ == 'False Positive')) +
    geom_col(mapping = aes(x = factor(cat, levels = c('paret', 'adapt', 'rando')),
                           fill = factor(cat, levels = c('paret', 'adapt', 'rando')), y = prob)) +
    geom_errorbar(mapping = aes(ymin = prob - err, ymax = prob + err,

data2$cat[data2$cat == 'start'] = '0paret'

data = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_ZDT4/GP_ImportanceRank.csv')
data$method[data$method == 'Marginalization'] = 'Method: Marginal'
data$method[data$method == 'Shapley Value'] = 'Method: Shapley'

# Fix Shapley value relative numbers - they were taken over the maximum, not the maximum absolute value
typ = unique(data$typ)
for(i in 1:length(typ)){
  data$r.import[data$method == 'Method: Shapley' & data$typ == typ[i]] = 
    abs(data$import[data$method == 'Method: Shapley' & data$typ == typ[i]]) / 
    max(abs(data$import[data$method == 'Method: Shapley' & data$typ == typ[i]]))
  data$r.sd[data$method == 'Method: Shapley' & data$typ == typ[i]] = 
    abs(data$sd[data$method == 'Method: Shapley' & data$typ == typ[i]]) / 
    max(abs(data$import[data$method == 'Method: Shapley' & data$typ == typ[i]]))
}

# Dummy data to extend ranges
dummy = expand.grid(c('Method: Shapley'), typ, unique(data$var))
names(dummy) = c('method', 'typ', 'var')
n = nrow(dummy); dummy = rbind(dummy, dummy)
dummy$r.import = 10; dummy$r.import[1:n] = -10
rm(typ, n)
ggplot(data) +
  geom_col(mapping = aes(x = var, y = r.import, fill = var)) +
  geom_errorbar(mapping = aes(x = var, ymax = r.import + r.sd, ymin = r.import - r.sd), width = 0.5) +
  geom_blank(data = dummy, mapping = aes(x = var, y = r.import)) +
  facet_rep_grid(method~typ, scales = 'free_y', repeat.tick.labels = TRUE, switch = 'y') + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = color.var) +
  plot.formatting() +
  theme(strip.placement = 'outside') +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.05))) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels = c(expression('x'[1]), expression('x'[2]), expression('x'[3]))) +
  labs(x = 'Variable', y = 'Relative Global Importance') +
  guides(fill = FALSE)

ggsave(filename = paste('Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
       dpi = 500, width = 90*1.5, height = 100*1.5, units = 'mm')

write.csv(data, file = paste('Data_Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '.csv', sep = ''))
fig.count = fig.count + 1

data.imp = data.imp[, !names(data.imp) %in% c('X', 'acid')]
names(data.imp)[names(data.imp) == 'Na.A'] = 'logNa'
data.all = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/GPar_AcidBase_data.csv')
# Convert to natural variables
data.nat = data.frame(pka1 = data.all$pka1,
                      pka2 = data.all$pka1 + data.all$pka2,
                      logA = data.all$logA,
                      logNa = data.all$logA + data.all$Na.A,
                      Energy.kJ.mol = data.all$Energy.kJ.mol,
                      Flux.mol.m2s = data.all$Flux.mol.m2s,
                      typ = data.all$typ)

# Obtain the Pareto front
data.all = rbind(data.nat[, names(data.nat) %in% names(data.imp)],
                 data.imp[, names(data.imp) %in% names(data.nat)])
# Updated Pareto front
test = as.matrix(data.all[data.all$Flux.mol.m2s > 0,
                          names(data.all) %in% c('Energy.kJ.mol', 'Flux.mol.m2s')])
# For the Pareto front determination, need both to minimize
test[,2] = -test[,2]
par.front = t(nondominated_points(points = t(test)))
par.front[,2] = -par.front[,2]
# Identify the conditions leading to the Pareto front
data.fnt = filter(data.all, Energy.kJ.mol %in% par.front[,1], Flux.mol.m2s %in% par.front[,2])
data.fnt$label = 'Pareto front'
data.imp = rbind(data.imp, data.fnt)
rm(data.fnt)

# Store data
write.csv(data.imp, file = paste('Data_Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '_PoI.csv', sep = ''))
write.csv(data.all, file = paste('Data_Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '_All.csv', sep = ''))

# MEA reference points:
MEA.flux = 2.2 #mmol/m2*s
MEA.ener = 110*0.35 #kJe/mol C

sz = 2
# Other lines of interest
reg.flux = data.frame(min.flux = MEA.flux*1e-3, max.flux = max(data.imp$Flux.mol.m2s)*1.1,
                     min.ener = min(data.imp$Energy.kJ.mol)*0.9,
                     max.ener = 45,
                     region = 'High Flux')
reg.ener = data.frame(min.flux = MEA.flux*1e-4,
                     max.flux = max(data.imp$Flux.mol.m2s)*1.1, 
                     min.ener = min(data.imp$Energy.kJ.mol)*0.9,
                     max.ener = mean(range(filter(data.imp, Flux.mol.m2s < 2.4e-3)$Energy.kJ.mol)),
                     region = 'Low Energy')
reg.MEA = data.frame(min.flux = MEA.flux*1e-4,
                     max.flux = max(data.imp$Flux.mol.m2s)*1.1, 
                     min.ener = min(data.imp$Energy.kJ.mol)*0.9,
                     max.ener = MEA.ener,
                     region = 'Competitive vs MEA')
write.csv(rbind(reg.flux, reg.ener, reg.MEA), 
          file = paste('Data_Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '_Bounds.csv', sep = ''))

sz = 2
ggplot() +
  # Regions of interest
  geom_rect(rbind(reg.flux, reg.ener), 
          mapping = aes(xmin = min.flux*1e3, xmax = max.flux*1e3, ymin = min.ener, ymax = max.ener, 
                        fill = region),
          linetype = 1, color = 'black', alpha = 0.3) +
  geom_rect(reg.MEA, 
          mapping = aes(xmin = min.flux*1e3, xmax = max.flux*1e3, ymin = min.ener, ymax = max.ener, 
                        fill = region),
          linetype = 2, color = 'black', alpha = 0, size = 1) +
  # All data
  geom_point(data = filter(data.nat, Flux.mol.m2s > 0, Energy.kJ.mol < 100),
             mapping = aes(x = Flux.mol.m2s*1e3, y = Energy.kJ.mol, shape = typ),
             size = sz, alpha = 0.5) +
  # Important points: first all together to get the legend order correct
  # geom_point(data = filter(data.imp, label != 'Pareto front'),
  #           mapping = aes(x = Flux.mol.m2s*1e3, y = Energy.kJ.mol, shape = typ, 
  #                         color = factor(label, levels = unique(label))),
  #           size = sz-1) +
  geom_line(data = filter(data.imp, label == 'Pareto front'),
            mapping = aes(x = Flux.mol.m2s*1e3, y = Energy.kJ.mol, color = label), size = sz-1) +
  geom_point(data = filter(data.imp, label == 'Pareto front'),
            mapping = aes(x = Flux.mol.m2s*1e3, y = Energy.kJ.mol, color = label), size = sz-1) +
  geom_point(data = filter(data.imp, label != 'Pareto front'),
            mapping = aes(x = Flux.mol.m2s*1e3, y = Energy.kJ.mol, color = 'Ref'), 
            shape = 13, size = sz + 2, stroke = sz-0.75) +
  # Box labels
  geom_label(rbind(reg.flux, reg.ener, reg.MEA),
            mapping = aes(x = min.flux*1e3, y = max.ener, 
                          label = c('Maximum Flux', 'Minimum Energy', 'Competitive vs MEA')),
            vjust = 1, hjust = 0, nudge_x = 0.025, nudge_y = -0.15,
            alpha = 0.75, fill = 'white') +
  # Labels and formatting
  labs(x = expression('Peak CO'[2]*' Flux (mmol/m'^2*'s)'), 
       y = expression('Minimum Energy Demand (kJ'['e']*'/mol C)'),
       shape = NULL) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(from = 0, to = 3.5, by = 0.5), limits = c(0, 3.5),
                     expand = expansion(mult = c(0.01, 0.01))) + 
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(from = 0, to = 75, by = 25), limits = c(0, 75),
                     expand = expansion(mult = c(0.01, 0.15))) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c('Ref' = color.cyc[1], 'Pareto front' = color.cyc[4]),
                     label = c('Ref' = 'Representative Points', 'Pareto front' = 'Pareto front'),
                     name = NULL) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('white', color.palet[c(1,3)]), 
                    name = 'Regions of Interest') +
  guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(shape = c(20, 13), linetype = c(1, 0))),
         shape = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = sz, color = 'black', alpha = 1)),
  # guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(shape = c(16, 17, 16, 20), linetype = c(0, 0, 0, 1))),
  #        shape = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = sz)),
         # fill = guide_legend(override.aes = list(alpha = c(0, 0.5, 0.5), linetype = c(2, 1, 1)))) +
         fill = FALSE) +
  plot.formatting() + 
  theme(legend.title = element_text(margin = margin(t = 5, unit = 'pt')),
        legend.position = c(1, 1)*0.95,
        legend.justification = c(1, 1)
        )

# FIgure 8: Importance ranking

# Load data
rank = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/ImportanceRanking.csv')
rank = rank[, names(rank) %in% c('var', 'rank', 'uncert', 'region')]
rank$var[rank$var == 'logA'] = 'log[Q]'
rank$region[rank$region == 'Full Viable Region'] = 'Competitive Performance'

# Normalize each region, then sort by rank
rank.norm = data.frame()
for(reg in unique(rank$region)){
    sub = filter(rank, region == reg)
    sub$uncert = sub$uncert/max(sub$rank)
    sub$rank   = sub$rank  /max(sub$rank)
    # Sort by rank
    rank.norm = rbind(rank.norm, sub[order(sub$rank, decreasing = TRUE), ])
}
rank.norm$x = 1:nrow(rank.norm)

nudge = 0.2
ggplot() +
  geom_col(rank.norm, mapping = aes(x = x, y = rank, fill = var)) +
  geom_errorbar(rank.norm, mapping = aes(x = x, ymin = rank - uncert, ymax = rank + uncert),
                width = 0.5, alpha = 0.5) +
  # Labels without subscripts
  geom_text(filter(rank.norm, !var %in% c('pka1', 'pka2', 'Na.A', 'Base')),
            mapping = aes(x = x, y = rank + uncert, label = var), nudge_y = nudge) +
  # Labels with subscripts
  geom_text(filter(rank.norm, var %in% 'pka1'),
            mapping = aes(x = x, y = rank + uncert),
            label = expression('p'*italic(K)['a,1']),
            nudge_y = nudge) +
  geom_text(filter(rank.norm, var %in% 'pka2'),
            mapping = aes(x = x, y = rank + uncert),
            label = expression('p'*italic(K)['a,2']),
            nudge_y = nudge) +
  # Labels with line breaks
  geom_text(filter(rank.norm, var %in% 'Na.A'),
            mapping = aes(x = x, y = rank + uncert),
            label = 'log[HX] or\nlog[MOH]',
            nudge_y = nudge, vjust = 0) +
  geom_text(filter(rank.norm, var %in% 'Base'),
            mapping = aes(x = x, y = rank + uncert),
            label = '+HX vs.\n+MOH',
            nudge_y = nudge, vjust = 0) +
  facet_wrap(~region, nrow = 3, scales = 'free_x') +
  # Labels and formatting
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('grey50', color.cyc)) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1)),
                     breaks = c(0, 1.6),
                     labels = c('Less', 'More')) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = NULL, labels = NULL) +
  labs(x = NULL, y = 'Relative Global Importance') +
  guides(fill = FALSE) +
  plot.formatting() +
  theme(strip.text = element_text(size = 13, hjust = 0))

rank$var[rank$var == 'Na.A'] = 'log{HX or MOH}'
rank$var[rank$var == 'Base'] = 'HX vs MOH'
write.csv(rank, file = paste('Data_Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '.csv', sep = ''))

ggsave(filename = paste('Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
       dpi = 500, width = 90*1.5, height = 68*1.5, units = 'mm')

fig.count = fig.count + 1

# Figure 9: 1D marginals and conditional marginals

# Load data
marg1D = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/1DMarginals.csv')
marg1D = marg1D[, !names(marg1D) %in% 'X']
marg1D = filter(marg1D, region == 'Full Viable Region')
# names(marg1D)
marg.cond = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/AcceptCondMargin.csv')
marg.cond = marg.cond[, !names(marg.cond) %in% 'X']
marg.cond$condition = 'Optimal'
marg.cond$marg.name[marg.cond$marg.name == 'logNa.A'] = 'log{Na}'
# names(marg.cond)

# Convert the 1D full conditionals into the same form as the optimal conditionals
marg1D.pka1 = data.frame(marg.p = c(marg1D$pa.pka1, marg1D$pb.pka1),
                         marg.s = c(marg1D$sa.pka1, marg1D$sb.pka1),
                         marg.var = marg1D$pka1, marg.name = 'pka1', condition = 'Full',
                         marg.typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg1D)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg1D)))
                         )
marg1D.pka2 = data.frame(marg.p = c(marg1D$pa.pka2, marg1D$pb.pka2),
                         marg.s = c(marg1D$sa.pka2, marg1D$sb.pka2),
                         marg.var = marg1D$pka2, marg.name = 'pka2', condition = 'Full',
                         marg.typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg1D)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg1D)))
                         )
marg1D.logA = data.frame(marg.p = c(marg1D$pa.logA, marg1D$pb.logA),
                         marg.s = c(marg1D$sa.logA, marg1D$sb.logA),
                         marg.var = marg1D$logA, marg.name = 'logA', condition = 'Full',
                         marg.typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg1D)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg1D)))
                         )
marg1D.logNa = data.frame(marg.p = c(marg1D$pa.Na.A, marg1D$pb.Na.A),
                         marg.s = c(marg1D$sa.Na.A, marg1D$sb.Na.A),
                         marg.var = marg1D$Na.A, marg.name = 'log{Na}', condition = 'Full',
                         marg.typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg1D)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg1D)))
                         )
# Combine
marg.all = rbind(marg.cond, marg1D.pka1, marg1D.pka2, marg1D.logA, marg1D.logNa)
# Update names
marg.all$marg.name[marg.all$marg.name == 'logA'] = 'log{Q}'
write.csv(marg.all, file = paste('Data_Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '.csv', sep = ''))
rm(marg1D, marg.cond, marg1D.pka1, marg1D.pka2, marg1D.logA, marg1D.logNa)

# Polygon for region of uncertainty
marg.uncert = data.frame(p = c(marg.all$marg.p + marg.all$marg.s,
                               rev(marg.all$marg.p - marg.all$marg.s)),
                         var = c(marg.all$marg.var, rev(marg.all$marg.var)),
                         condition = c(marg.all$condition, rev(marg.all$condition)),
                         marg.name = c(marg.all$marg.name, rev(marg.all$marg.name)),
                         marg.typ = c(marg.all$marg.typ, rev(marg.all$marg.typ)))
# Bound the uncertainty within probabilities
marg.uncert$p[marg.uncert$p < 0] = 0
marg.uncert$p[marg.uncert$p > 1] = 1

sz = 1
g.pka2 = ggplot() +
    geom_polygon(data = filter(marg.uncert, marg.name %in% 'pka2'),
              mapping = aes(x = var, y = p, 
                            fill = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition))), alpha = 0.3) +
    geom_path(data = filter(marg.all, marg.name %in% 'pka2'),
              mapping = aes(x = marg.var, y = marg.p, 
                            color = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition)),
                            linetype = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition))), size = sz) +
    facet_rep_grid(~marg.typ, scales = 'free', repeat.tick.labels = 'x') +
    labs(x = expression('p'*italic(K)['a,2']), y = NULL, color = 'Conditions', linetype = 'Conditions') +
    scale_color_manual(values = color.cyc[c(1,2)]) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1))) +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(from = 3, to = 18, by = 3),
                       labels = seq(from = 3, to = 18, by = 3),
                       limits = c(2, 20)) +
    plot.formatting() + guides(fill = FALSE) +
    theme(axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = -5, b = 5, unit = 'pt')))
g.pka1 = ggplot() +
    geom_polygon(data = filter(marg.uncert, marg.name %in% 'pka1'),
              mapping = aes(x = var, y = p, 
                            fill = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition))), alpha = 0.3) +
    geom_path(data = filter(marg.all, marg.name %in% 'pka1'),
              mapping = aes(x = marg.var, y = marg.p, 
                            color = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition)),
                            linetype = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition))), size = sz) +
    facet_rep_grid(~marg.typ, scales = 'free', repeat.tick.labels = 'x') +
    labs(x = expression('p'*italic(K)['a,1']), y = NULL, color = 'Conditions', linetype = 'Conditions') +
    scale_color_manual(values = color.cyc[c(1,2)]) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1))) +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(from = 3, to = 18, by = 3),
                       labels = seq(from = 3, to = 18, by = 3),
                       limits = c(2, 20)) +
    guides(fill = FALSE) +
    plot.formatting() + theme(strip.text = element_blank(), strip.background = element_blank(),
                              axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = -5, b = 5, unit = 'pt')))
g.logQ = ggplot() +
    geom_polygon(data = filter(marg.uncert, marg.name %in% 'log{Q}'),
              mapping = aes(x = var, y = p, 
                            fill = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition))), alpha = 0.3) +
    geom_path(data = filter(marg.all, marg.name %in% 'log{Q}'),
              mapping = aes(x = marg.var, y = marg.p, 
                            color = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition)),
                            linetype = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition))), size = sz) +
    facet_rep_grid(~marg.typ, scales = 'free', repeat.tick.labels = 'x') +
    labs(x = expression('log'[10]*'{Quinone (M)}'), 
         y = 'Probability of Competitive Performance', color = 'Conditions', linetype = 'Conditions') +
    scale_color_manual(values = color.cyc[c(1,2)]) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1))) +
    guides(fill = FALSE) +
    plot.formatting() + theme(strip.text = element_blank(), strip.background = element_blank(),
                              axis.title.y = element_text(hjust = 0.125),
                              axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = -5, b = 5, unit = 'pt')))
g.logNa = ggplot() +
    geom_polygon(data = filter(marg.uncert, marg.name %in% 'log{Na}'),
              mapping = aes(x = var, y = p, 
                            fill = factor(condition, levels = unique(condition))), alpha = 0.3) +
    geom_path(data = filter(marg.all, marg.name %in% 'log{Na}'),

    facet_rep_grid(~marg.typ, scales = 'free', repeat.tick.labels = 'x') +
    labs(x = expression('log'[10]*'{Acid or Base (M)}'), y = NULL, color = 'Conditions', linetype = 'Conditions') +
    scale_color_manual(values = color.cyc[c(1,2)]) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1))) +
    guides(fill = FALSE) +
    plot.formatting() + theme(strip.text = element_blank(), strip.background = element_blank(),
                              axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = -5, b = 5, unit = 'pt')))
g.pka2 / g.pka1 / g.logQ / g.logNa + plot_layout(guides = 'collect')

             mapping = aes(y = Energy.kJ.mol, x = 1e3*Flux.mol.m2s,

             size = sz, alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_line(filter(GPar.front.pKa, Flux.mol.m2s > 0, Energy.kJ.mol < 100),
            mapping = aes(y = Energy.kJ.mol, x = 1e3*Flux.mol.m2s, color = as.factor(pkaDif)),
            size = sz*0.6) +
  geom_point(filter(GPar.front.pKa, Flux.mol.m2s > 0, Energy.kJ.mol < 100),
             mapping = aes(y = Energy.kJ.mol, x = 1e3*Flux.mol.m2s, 
                           color = as.factor(pkaDif), shape = as.factor(pkaDif)),
             size = sz) +
  labs(x = NULL, y = NULL, color = expression('Max p'*italic(K)['a']*' Difference'),
       shape = expression('Max p'*italic(K)['a']*' Difference')) +
  plot.formatting() + scale_x_continuous(limits = bounds) +
  scale_color_manual(values = color.shift)
g.top / g.bot

write.csv(GPar.front.pKa, file = paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), 'b.csv', sep = ''))

# Load data

marg.cond$condition = 'Optimal'
marg.cond$marg.name[marg.cond$marg.name == 'logNa.A'] = 'log{Na}'
# names(marg.cond)

                         marg.s = c(marg1D$sa.pka1, marg1D$sb.pka1),
                         marg.var = marg1D$pka1, marg.name = 'pka1', condition = 'Full',
                         marg.typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg1D)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg1D)))
                         )
marg1D.pka2 = data.frame(marg.p = c(marg1D$pa.pka2, marg1D$pb.pka2),
                         marg.s = c(marg1D$sa.pka2, marg1D$sb.pka2),
                         marg.var = marg1D$pka2, marg.name = 'pka2', condition = 'Full',
                         marg.typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg1D)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg1D)))
                         )

                         marg.s = c(marg1D$sa.logA, marg1D$sb.logA),

                         marg.typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg1D)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg1D)))
                         )
marg1D.logNa = data.frame(marg.p = c(marg1D$pa.Na.A, marg1D$pb.Na.A),

                         marg.typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg1D)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg1D)))

marg = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/1DMarginals_Relative.csv')
base = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/AcidBaseMarginal_Relative.csv')

# Acid/base comparison
typ = rep('+Acid', nrow(base))
typ[base$typ == 1] = '+Base'
base$typ = typ
rm(typ)
base = base[, !names(base) %in% c('X', 'sd')]
names(base) = c('typ', 'prob', 'var', 'lower', 'upper', 'region')
base$region[base$region == 'Full Viable Region'] = 'Competitive Performance'

# Map only the relative variables
marg.pka.diff = data.frame(val = marg$pka2,
                           prob = c(marg$pa.pka2, marg$pb.pka2),
                           sd = c(marg$sa.pka2, marg$sb.pka2),
                           var = 'pKaDiff',
                           reg = marg$region,
                           typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg))))
marg.Na.rat = data.frame(val = marg$Na.A,
                           prob = c(marg$pa.Na.A, marg$pb.Na.A),
                           sd = c(marg$sa.Na.A, marg$sb.Na.A),
                           reg = marg$region,
                           var = 'NaQRatio',
                           typ = c(rep('+Acid', nrow(marg)), rep('+Base', nrow(marg))))
marg = rbind(marg.pka.diff, marg.Na.rat)
marg.range = data.frame(var = c(marg$var, rev(marg$var)),
                        val = c(marg$val, rev(marg$val)),
                        typ = c(marg$typ, rev(marg$typ)),
                        reg = c(marg$reg, rev(marg$reg)),
                        prob = c(marg$prob + marg$sd, rev(marg$prob - marg$sd)) )
marg.range$prob[marg.range$prob > 1] = 1
marg.range$prob[marg.range$prob < 0] = 0

g.base = ggplot(base) +
  geom_col(mapping = aes(x = region, y = prob, fill = region)) +
  geom_errorbar(mapping = aes(x = region, ymin = lower, ymax = upper), width = 0.5) +
  facet_rep_wrap(~typ) +
  labs(x = '+Acid or +Base', y = NULL, fill = '') +
  plot.formatting() + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = color.palet) +
  scale_x_discrete(breaks = NULL) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.05)))

g.pka = ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = filter(marg.range, var == 'pKaDiff'), mapping = aes(x = val, y = prob, fill = reg), 
               alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_path(data = filter(marg, var == 'pKaDiff'), mapping = aes(x = val, y = prob, color = reg)) +
  facet_rep_grid(~typ, repeat.tick.labels = 'x') +
  plot.formatting() +
  theme(strip.text = element_blank(), strip.background = element_blank(),
        axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = -5, b = 5, unit = 'pt'))) +
  guides(fill = FALSE, color = FALSE) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = color.palet) +
  scale_color_manual(values = color.palet) +
  labs(x = expression('Difference in p'*italic(K)['a']), y = 'Probability\n[Region of Interest]')
g.Na = ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = filter(marg.range, var == 'NaQRatio'), mapping = aes(x = val, y = prob, fill = reg), 
               alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_path(data = filter(marg, var == 'NaQRatio'), mapping = aes(x = val, y = prob, color = reg)) +
  facet_rep_grid(~typ, repeat.tick.labels = 'x') +
  plot.formatting() +
  theme(strip.text = element_blank(), strip.background = element_blank(),
        axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = -5, b = 5, unit = 'pt'))) + 
  guides(fill = FALSE, color = FALSE) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = color.palet) +
  scale_color_manual(values = color.palet) +
  labs(x = expression('log'[10]*' {HX or MOH}/{Quinone}'), y = NULL)


g.base / g.pka / g.Na + plot_layout(guides = 'collect')

write.csv(base, file = paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), 'a.csv', sep = ''))
write.csv(marg, file = paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), 'bc.csv', sep = ''))
ggsave(filename = paste('FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
       dpi = 500, width = 140*1.5, height = 105*1.5, units = 'mm')

rm(g.base, g.pka, g.Na)
impo = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/ImportanceRanking_Relative.csv')
impo = impo[, !names(impo) %in% c('rng', 'area', 'sd')]
impo$var[impo$var == 'logA'] = 'log{Q}'
impo$region[impo$region == 'Full Viable Region'] = 'Competitive Performance'

imp.norm = data.frame()
for(reg in unique(impo$region)){
  sub = filter(impo, region == reg)
  sub$r.sd = sub$uncert/max(sub$rank)
  sub$r.rank = sub$rank/max(sub$rank)
  # Sort
  sub = sub[order(sub$r.rank, decreasing = TRUE), ]
  sub$X = 1:5
  imp.norm = rbind(imp.norm, sub)
}

nudge = 0.15
ggplot() +
  geom_col(imp.norm, mapping = aes(x = X, y = r.rank, fill = var)) +
  geom_errorbar(imp.norm, mapping = aes(x = X, ymin = r.rank - r.sd, ymax = r.rank + r.sd),
                width = 0.5, alpha = 0.5) +
  facet_wrap(~region, nrow = 3, scales = 'free_x') +
  # Labels without subscripts
  geom_text(filter(imp.norm, !var %in% c('pka1', 'pka2', 'Na.A', 'Base')), 
            mapping = aes(x = X, y = r.rank + r.sd, label = var), nudge_y = nudge) +
  # Labels with subscripts
  geom_text(filter(imp.norm, var %in% 'pka1'), 
            mapping = aes(x = X, y = r.rank + r.sd), 
            label = expression('p'*italic(K)['a,1']),
            nudge_y = nudge) +
  geom_text(filter(imp.norm, var %in% 'pka2'), 
            mapping = aes(x = X, y = r.rank + r.sd), 
            label = expression('p'*italic(K)['a']*' Diff.'),
            nudge_y = nudge) +
  # Labels with line breaks
  geom_text(filter(imp.norm, var %in% 'Na.A'), 
            mapping = aes(x = X, y = r.rank + r.sd), 
            label = '{HX}:{Q} or \n{MOH}:{Q}',
            nudge_y = nudge, vjust = 0) +
  geom_text(filter(imp.norm, var %in% 'Base'), 
            mapping = aes(x = X, y = r.rank + r.sd), 
            label = 'Acid or\nBase',
            nudge_y = nudge, vjust = 0) +
  # Labels and formatting
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('grey50', color.cyc)) +
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1)),
                     breaks = c(0, 1.6),
                     labels = c('Less', 'More')) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = NULL, labels = NULL) +
  labs(x = NULL, y = 'Relative Importance') +
  guides(fill = FALSE) +
  plot.formatting() +
  theme(strip.text = element_text(size = 13, hjust = 0))

group.dist = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/SubstEffect.csv')

# Filter to only the first of each numeric group

                           filter(group.dist, str == i)[1,])

quinone.data = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/PCET/PCET_Process/QuinoneProbs.csv')
quinone.data

groups = unique(c(quinone.data$R2, quinone.data$R3, quinone.data$R5, quinone.data$R6))
# Not concerned with the hydrogen case
# groups = groups[-c(groups %in% 'H')]
groups

# Classifying the groups according to donoating/withdrawing and relative strength (using the standard ladder)
type = c('Reference', 'Donating', 'Donating', 'Donating', 'Donating', 'Donating', 'Donating', 'Donating',
         'Donating', 'Donating', 'Withdrawing', 'Withdrawing', 'Withdrawing', '?', '?', 'Withdrawing',
         'Withdrawing', 'Withdrawing', 'Withdrawing', 'Withdrawing', 'Withdrawing', 'Withdrawing', 'Withdrawing')
str = c(0, 2, 3, 3, 6, 9, 8, 3, 7, 6, -1, -1, -1, NA, NA, -2, -4, -7, -8, -5, -8, -12, -3)

# Find average probability if any substitutions are of that functional group
group.dist = data.frame()
for(i in 1:length(groups)){
  subst = groups[i]
  # Probability of being viable
  p.viable = c(filter(quinone.data, R2 == subst)$p.accept, filter(quinone.data, R3 == subst)$p.accept,
               filter(quinone.data, R5 == subst)$p.accept, filter(quinone.data, R6 == subst)$p.accept)
  # Standard reduction potentials
  e1 = c(filter(quinone.data, R2 == subst)$E0.1, filter(quinone.data, R3 == subst)$E0.1,
         filter(quinone.data, R5 == subst)$E0.1, filter(quinone.data, R6 == subst)$E0.1)
  e2 = c(filter(quinone.data, R2 == subst)$E0.2, filter(quinone.data, R3 == subst)$E0.2,
         filter(quinone.data, R5 == subst)$E0.2, filter(quinone.data, R6 == subst)$E0.2)
  
  group.dist = rbind(group.dist, 
                     data.frame(group = subst, probs = p.viable,
                                E01 = e1, E02 = e2,
                                type = type[i], str = str[i]) )
}
# Note that it is a functional group and not a molecule
group.dist$group = paste('-', group.dist$group, sep = '')
# Update for labels
group.dist.lab = data.frame()
for(i in unique(group.dist$str)){
    group.dist.lab = rbind(group.dist.lab,
                           filter(group.dist, str == i)[1,])
}
group.lab = c("-H", expression("-C"[6]*"H"[5]), expression("-CH"[3]), expression("-OCH"[3]),
                             expression("-N(CH"[3]*")"[2]), expression("-NH"[2]), "-OH", "-X",
                             "-CHO", expression("-COOCH"[3]), expression("-CF"[3]), "-CN", "-COOH", 
                             expression("-NO"[2]), expression("-COCH"[3]))

# Font size
sz = 3.5
# Plots
ggplot() +
    geom_boxplot(filter(group.dist, is.na(str) == FALSE),
                 mapping = aes(x = (str), y = probs, fill = type, group = str), color = 'black', 
                 alpha = 0.5, weight = 20) +
    geom_text(filter(group.dist.lab, is.na(str) == FALSE),
              mapping = aes(x = str, y = 0.8), label = group.lab, 
              hjust = 0, size = sz) +
    labs(x = 'Substituent Effect', y = 'Probability of\nCompetitive Performance', x = '', fill = '') +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(-13, 0, 10),
               labels = c('More\nWithdrawing', '', 'More\nDonating'),
               limits = c(-13.2, 10.2)) +
    scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, 1),
                       breaks = seq(from = 0, to = 0.8, by = 0.2),
                       expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.05))) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = color.palet,
                      name = 'Net Effect') +
    plot.formatting() + 
    theme(#axis.title.x = element_text(hjust = 0.7),
          axis.title.y = element_text(margin = margin(r = -10, unit = 'mm')),
          legend.position = 'top', legend.margin = margin(l = -20, unit = 'mm'),
          plot.margin = margin(l = 8, unit = 'mm')) +
    coord_flip()
ggsave(filename = paste('Fig', sprintf('%02d', fig.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
       dpi = 500, width = 90*1.5, height = 80*1.5, units = 'mm')

g1 = ggplot() +
    geom_boxplot(filter(group.dist, is.na(str) == FALSE),
                 mapping = aes(x = (str), y = E01, fill = type, group = str), color = 'black', 
                 alpha = 0.5, weight = 20) +
    labs(x = 'Substituent Effect', y = 'First Reduction\nPotential (V vs SHE)', x = '', fill = '') +
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = c(-13, 0, 10),
               labels = c('More\nWithdrawing', '', 'More\nDonating'),

    plot.formatting() +

g2 = ggplot() +

data1 = rbind(data1, read.csv('../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_Quartic/Margin_SVM_dist.csv'))
data1$typ = 'Pareto Distance'

data2 = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/Ex_Quartic/Marginals_cutof.csv')
data2$method = 'GP'
data2 = rbind(data2, read.csv('../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_Quartic/Margin_SVM_cutof.csv'))
data2$typ = 'Threshold Cutoff'

data3 = read.csv('../BayesOptTol/Ex_Quartic/Marginals_radan.csv')
data3$method = 'GP'
data3 = rbind(data3, read.csv('../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_Quartic/Margin_SVM_radan.csv'))
data3$typ = 'Utopia Distance'

data = rbind(data1, data2, data3)
rm(data1, data2, data3)
# Fix order of the datasets
data$cat[data$cat == 'start'] = '0start'
data$cat[data$cat == 'adapt'] = '1adapt'
data$cat[data$cat == 'rando'] = '2rando'

write.csv(data, file = paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), '.csv', sep = ''))

# Re-configure the true result to account for the Monte Carlo uncertainty in the estimate
data.tru = filter(data, cat == 'tru')
data.tru = data.frame(x = c(data.tru$x, rev(data.tru$x)),
                      p = c(data.tru$prob + data.tru$psd, rev(data.tru$prob - data.tru$psd)),
                      typ = c(data.tru$typ, rev(data.tru$typ)),
                      var = c(data.tru$var, rev(data.tru$var)))
data.tru

sz = 0.75
gS3a = ggplot() +
    geom_polygon(filter(data.tru, var == 'x1'), 
                 mapping = aes(x = x, y = p), fill = 'grey25', alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_line(filter(data, var == 'x1', cat != 'tru'),
              mapping = aes(x = x, y = prob, color = cat, linetype = cat), size = sz) +
    scale_color_manual(name = '',
                       breaks = c('0start', '1adapt', '2rando'),
                       labels = c('0start' = 'Start', 
                                 '1adapt' = 'Start + \nAdaptive Sampling', 
                                 '2rando' = 'Start + \nRandom Sampling'),
                       values = color.palet) +
    scale_linetype_discrete(name = '',
                       breaks = c('0start', '1adapt', '2rando'),
                       labels = c('0start' = 'Start', 
                                 '1adapt' = 'Start + \nAdaptive Sampling', 
                                 '2rando' = 'Start + \nRandom Sampling')) +
    plot.formatting() + 
    facet_rep_grid(typ~method, labeller = labeller(typ = label_wrap_gen(10))) +
    theme(legend.position = 'bottom', legend.direction = 'horizontal',
          panel.spacing.y = unit(0, "lines"),
          panel.spacing.x = unit(-0.05, "lines")) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1), expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0))) +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0))) +
    labs(x = expression('x'[1]), y = 'Probability of Acceptance', subtitle = 'a)')

gS3b = ggplot() +
    geom_polygon(filter(data.tru, var == 'x2'), 
                 mapping = aes(x = x, y = p), fill = 'grey25', alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_line(filter(data, var == 'x2', cat != 'tru'),
              mapping = aes(x = x, y = prob, color = cat, linetype = cat), size = sz) +
    scale_color_manual(name = '',
                       breaks = c('0start', '1adapt', '2rando'),
                       labels = c('0start' = 'Start', 
                                 '1adapt' = 'Start + \nAdaptive Sampling', 
                                 '2rando' = 'Start + \nRandom Sampling'),
                       values = color.palet) +
    scale_linetype_discrete(name = '',
                       breaks = c('0start', '1adapt', '2rando'),
                       labels = c('0start' = 'Start', 
                                 '1adapt' = 'Start + \nAdaptive Sampling', 
                                 '2rando' = 'Start + \nRandom Sampling')) +
    facet_rep_grid(typ~method, labeller = labeller(typ = label_wrap_gen(10))) +
    plot.formatting() + 
    theme(legend.position = 'bottom', legend.direction = 'horizontal',
          panel.spacing.y = unit(0, "lines"),
          panel.spacing.x = unit(-0.05, "lines")) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1), expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0))) +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0))) +
    labs(x = expression('x'[2]), y = 'Probability of Acceptance', subtitle = 'b)')

gS3a / gS3b + plot_layout(guides = 'collect') & 
  theme(legend.position = 'right', legend.direction = 'vertical')
ggsave(filename = paste('FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
         dpi = 500, width = 140*1.5, height = 120*2, units = 'mm')

SI.count = SI.count + 1

# Figure 3: 1D marginalization R^2 compared to the real result. Rows: Different criteria. Columns: classification model. Colors: before/after/random sampling.

# Load data
data1 = read.csv(file = '../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_Quartic/Marginals_CoefDet_delta.csv')
data1$typ = 'Pareto Distance'
data2 = read.csv(file = '../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_Quartic/Marginals_CoefDet_cutof.csv')
data2$typ = 'Threshold Cutoff'
data3 = read.csv(file = '../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_Quartic/Marginals_CoefDet_radan.csv')
data3$typ = 'Utopia Distance'
data = rbind(data1, data2, data3)
rm(data1, data2, data3)

# data

ggplot(data) +
    geom_col(mapping = aes(y = coef-0.4, x = dataset, fill = dataset)) +
    facet_rep_grid(typ~method, scales = 'free_x', switch = 'y') +
    scale_fill_manual(name = NULL,
                      labels = c('Start', 'Start + Adaptive Sampling', 'Start + Random Sampling'),
                      values = color.palet) +
    plot.formatting() +
    theme(panel.spacing.y = unit(0, "lines"),
          strip.placement = 'outside',
          panel.spacing.x = unit(0.00001, "lines"),
          legend.position = 'bottom', legend.direction = 'horizontal',
          legend.box.margin = margin(r = 15, unit = 'mm'),
          axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = 5, unit = 'pt'))) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.1)),
                       breaks = c(0, 0.3, 0.6),
                       labels = c(0.4, 0.7, 1)) +
    scale_x_discrete(labels = NULL) +
    labs(x = 'Training Data: ', y = '1D Marginal Coefficient of Determination')
ggsave(filename = paste('FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
         dpi = 500, width = 135, height = 120, units = 'mm')

write.csv(data, file = paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), '.csv', sep = ''))
SI.count = SI.count + 1

# Figure 2: Importance rankings with uncertainties. Rows: selection criteria. Columns: Importance method.

# Load data
data = read.csv(file = '../BayesOptTol/MLMethodTests_Quartic/ImportRank_Method.csv')
data

data$method = paste('Method: ', data$method, sep = '')
ggplot(data) +
    geom_col(mapping = aes(group = var, y = r.import, fill = var, x = model), position = 'dodge') +
    geom_errorbar(mapping = aes(x = model, group = var, ymin = r.import - r.sd, ymax = r.import + r.sd),
                  position = 'dodge', width = 0.9) +
    facet_rep_grid(method~typ, scales = 'free', repeat.tick.labels = 'x', switch = 'y') +
    scale_fill_manual(name = 'Variable', labels = c(expression('x'[1]), expression('x'[2])),
                        values = color.var[1:2]) +
    scale_x_discrete(labels = c('GP', 'pol' = 'SVM\n-pol', 'rad' = 'SVM\n-rad')) +
    plot.formatting() +
    theme(panel.spacing.y = unit(0.05, "lines"),
          panel.spacing.x = unit(-0.75, "lines"),
          strip.placement = 'outside',
          legend.position = 'top', legend.direction = 'horizontal',
          legend.box.margin = margin(r = 15, unit = 'mm'),
          legend.margin = margin(t = 0)) +
    scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, 0.05))) +
    labs(x = 'Model', y = 'Relative Global Importance')
ggsave(filename = paste('FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), '.tiff', sep = ''),
         dpi = 500, width = 135, height = 120, units = 'mm')

write.csv(data, file = paste('Data_FigS', sprintf('%02d', SI.count), '.csv', sep = ''))
SI.count = SI.count + 1
